'Cangjie programming language_entry_program_entry': 'In Cangjie code language, The entry point of a Cangjie program is the main function, which must be defined in the top-level of a package in the source file root directory. There can be at most one main function in the top-level of the root directory package. The main function cannot be modified by access modifiers, and it will not be imported when a package is imported.
The main function can have no parameters or accept an Array<String> as a parameter. Its return type can be Unit or an integer type.'

Code_Example:
// main.cj   without arguments:
main(): Int64 { // Ok.
    return 0
}
// main.cj  <String> Parameter type is Array main:
main(args: Array<String>): Unit { // Ok.
    for (arg in args) {
        println(arg)
    }
}

'Cangjie programming language_entry_main_function_requirements': 'In Cangjie code language, The main function must be defined in the top-level of the root directory package.
It cannot be modified by access modifiers.
It can have no parameters or accept an Array<String> as a parameter.
Its return type must be Unit or an integer type.'

Error_case_code:
// main.cj
main(): String { // Error, return type of 'main' is not 'Integer' or 'Unit'.
    return ""
}

// main.cj
main(args: Array<Int8>): Int64 { // Error, 'main' cannot be defined with parameter whose type is not Array<String>.
    return 0
}

// main.cj
// Error, multiple 'main's are found in source files.
main(args: Array<String>): Int32 {
    return 0
}

main(): Int8 {
    return 0
}
